        <bioghist id="ref2">
            <head>Biographical/Historical note</head>
            <p>John Gellatly was a resident of Brooklyn, New York, having emigrated to the United States aboard the ship 
                <emph render="italic">John Hale</emph> from Greenock, Scotland in 1835.</p>
        </bioghist>
        <scopecontent id="ref1">
            <head>Scope and Contents note</head>
            <p>The collection consists of 2 diaries, dated 1852-1856, kept by John Gellatly of Brooklyn. Entries include short notes on the weather and his daily activities, including names of people with whom he socialized.</p>
